                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14465662" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 24 Nov 2008 13:53:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the patches for 1.6-RC-1 and 1.7-beta-1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Its root cause was similar to that of the issue reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3165&quot; title=&quot;Regression in assignment of single character strings to char array element&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-3165&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-3165&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The implementation of ObjectArrayPutAtMetaMethod.invoke() had logically deviated from what was implemented in &quot;DefaultGroovyMethods-&amp;gt;putAt(Object[] array...)&quot; because of which auto-conversion between number types had got affected, some more examples of which are :-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Short[] shorts = &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1, 2, 3, 4, 5&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
shorts&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; = 50&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Float[] floats = &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1.0f, 2.0f, 3.0f, 4.0f, 5.0f&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
floats&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; = 50.0d&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14465895" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2008 15:31:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Roshan, how about applying the fix?I would fix he cases with Short and Float too, or not?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14465990" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2008 23:05:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patches have already been applied on 1.6.x and trunk alongwith a test for it making sure that in addition to the reported Integer to Byte conversion, other related conversions are also covered and tested. Marking it as fixed now as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3173&quot; title=&quot;Assignment to array elements is inconsistent with assignment to fields and variables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-3173&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-3173&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; remains open for the remaining regression issues related to assignment to array elements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
